[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring initialization options**\n\nI’m thinking about initializing elSpec using `readObject` with a custom data stream. It sounds like a neat approach, but I want to ensure that it's set up correctly to avoid issues later. I'll have to consider how the custom data will be structured, and if there are any potential pitfalls to watch out for. Alright, it's time to dive into the specifics and see what I might tweak to make this work optimally!\n\n**Considering serialization of BigInteger**\n\nI'm thinking about how to serialize BigInteger objects. After looking at class descriptions like TC_OBJECT and TC_REFERENCE, I realize I need to create a byte array to hold the serialized data. By using ObjectOutputStream's writeObject method on each object—like X, P, and G—I can write them out. But I have to keep in mind that this includes the stream magic header, which complicates things a bit. I'll need to account for that in my implementation.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0657d908e772fe5f0169fc0ff9e33881a39f09162d7c04181d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_BAUVK4kWWaU3Lp2gD1MbIiPTWIoF8eMo2UjPzYHyqiKgfFMdZ1Enf331G8Ik8WoiBJRrByW2GPeD_4_1ZYDXkzgmlHPo9G3cV4RUiL8lx_6i13_I-sooEzShcKvZW_xHX0IlcbsUKUDoEw_K_afxR7EYtOB1Ua1UG6QAb4Cdmvue7_GMZAqB0cG962weeLb-QEhRvC7KFLfiBASkE0aEl5g9gOIh882laTozdkpDsoaaL6CBshMLDgxiJaqOwmNB93dlNq46wXQNIVOruzXlYEhj52vkpc03GDZDg8NwLaXfHcXyCmWzANsMkb070DiA33V4XnLJrImgc5wXq0MKMa2EKzGrXTtpQDQmS5n0uyIm3N4G-omWP2K2dDNiDi6YVB5sY5rkd9M6A6734p5yhZ9Au6BPUfgmPDNmwmU_CM0vozucsQLe2RwKxKcihlFS14tONtag-J8_CPwFLBaNxVKUXrimJyHocDyP_NQ9_CKKhGkkN66Lv-Z367NkDg6-RqiwvZVVnwq4IMdAjI3ITxjkpqvVibXNfIywTQ-AC2ww2mDkc3wet4LWxGI4SwU-hOjFQBP700_dzxOUu2Sg25VI6qv0mZnjm_bY5QHX2Jb0EqcYyT-YQPrizprstYOReIcTQGMM4jo6YgILYKmmMIpKrMTSuCGsPbKdE5dwhmMZmKDCgI0kcDhyDDGaso6iZ9bnL_RDAWzQZmB5berTjG6TdbKSoIsMEiMkN2HZy3w9nzEKIyvYAzHabvvLQazqSi7M-Ay8DwD_Nfyd-JCrPFVtXGx